title: For Sale:  Real Maadi AK-47 Great condition
postcontent: This is a real Maadi ,made by Maadi 100% ARM model imported by AAC in Tennessee  . This was the ARM model that was built in Egypt , not USA. This is not a MISR-10 or MISR-90 made by CAI that was manufactured on crap receivers.  This is one of the last import 100% Maadi's that  that the Egyptians built.  They got it passed import restrictions by selling it in a sporter style with the thumb whole stock instead of a pistol grip.  This is also one of the rarer ones that came with the threaded barrel . the PARS imports had the threads removed  to get around import issues but the TENN imports came with all original ARM model threaded barrel with a cap tack welded on that was easily removed.  This is the 16" barrel model. This is also in extremely good condition for a Maadi.  It has maybe 200 rounds down the pipe since new and it still has a clean, shiny, factory paint job looking surprisingly well.   It now has REAL Maadi preban furniture on it but comes with ALL original sporter configuration parts including original Maadi thumbhole.   The factory actually left the bayo lug pretty much intact, so it really is a nice,preban style rifle.   Again , this is not a rifle built on old Norinco kits using Maadi parts  ( MISR-90) or a SPUD receiver American built Maadi Demilled kits (MISR -10).  This rifle has been brought back to Maadi Preban configuration. Has 922r parts (g2 trigger etc). Comes with 2 mags.  Probably won't see one this nice , defanged, with all original parts again.  THIS model was built on Russian AK machinery and tooling    The Egyptians were trained by the Russians. The Russians also hung around and oversaw the production of the Maadi AK. The real Maadi AK's are the closest most people can get to owning a real tooled Russian AKM rifle because of the Maadi factory ties with the Russian Military.

title: For Trade:  Norinco AK-47 Type 56 Vietnam War Retro Clone Converted Mak-90
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is my converted Norinco Mak-90. I have installed a Bakelite pistol grip and NOS Polytec Chu wood buttstock to make this an exact clone of the rifle US soldiers fought against in Vietnam minus the folding bayonet. It looks like someone picked the rifle right off the battlefield. The rifle is 22 years old and has been used. Blueing is generally thin on mak's, and as this is patterned after a production military rifle, function is the priority over cleaned up tool marks. The handguard and bluing show wear, but are in good used condition with NO rust.

The rifle is 922r compliant.

This has a lot of features found on AK-47's that modern AKM's omit or change. The dust cover is smooth and there is no clunky scope mount on the receiver. The gas tube is vented like an original AK. The trigger is double hook Tapco's G2 and has a 4.5lb smooth pull. The wood is all original Chinese. The barrel is heavy and chrome lined. The muzzle is not threaded and has no muzzle brake like an original AK.  The receiver is thick stamped 1.5mm steel. This is no flimsy WASR. These were banned from import in 1994.
Included free of charge is the original Mak-90 thumbhole stock for use as firewood or paperweight. An original 1970's dated Type 56 sling is included.

The Polytec Legend is widely considered to be the finest stamped AK ever made available in the US. The difference between that gun and this one is that this one says Mak-90 Sporter on the side and was made four years later in the same factory with the same parts.

The rifle is $850 cash by itself with 1 magazine. I will pay the transfer fee here at Norpoint.
For an extra $50 I will include a new ATI folding and collapsable stock set with rails.
For an extra $50 I will include 5 used once Tapco slab side magazines.

I will also accept 43 US silver dollars in trade.

Communication through Email only. Phone numbers will be ignored. This is so everything is understood and in writing. Have pictures available of your item for trade. My version of 80% condition and yours are probably vastly different. I use the NRA grading scale. I don't want new friends, just new guns.

More pictures are available. I will ship to your FFL where legal.

title: For Sale:  WWII GERMAN MAUSER KAR98K K98 K98K Kar98
postcontent:
This Kar98 is a Russian Capture but the bolt matches and it's only 2 numbers away from the rifle. The wood is an excellent white glue laminate. The code of this rifle is 147 which makes it a JP Saur & Sohn, Suhl. This particular rifle is a d block made in 1939. It still has the waffenamts and none have been scrubbed. The bore of this rifle is excellent +. You couldn't ask for a better bore. It cycles flawlessly and functions flawlessly. The import mark is very small below the muzzle near the bayonet lug. I recently put 30 rounds through it and it's extremely accurate. It does come with a reproduction sling dated 1940. It also has a cleaning rod as well. The wood stock is also marked with eagle and swastika and has the Heer h for Wehrmacht. I have done some research on the 147 code and I have read that all the rifles with this code in 1939 definitely went to the eastern front. Pretty cool to note.
